edu.csupomona.cs.cs141.thehouse

Class GameObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.csupomona.cs.cs141.thehouse.GameObject
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<GameObject>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Enemy, ExtraAmmo, Player, PlayerControl, Radar, Room, Shield

    public class GameObject
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<GameObject>, java.io.Serializable
    This method is the super class for all game objects: Player, Enemy, Shield, Room, Radar, and ExtraAmmo. Its primary function is to ensure that they can interact with each other and the Grid appropriately.
    Author:
    Andrew Niklas, Andrew Nipp, Ben Nickerson
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • roomExists

        public boolean roomExists(int xPosition2,
                          int i)
        This method checks to see if there is a room at the given location passed to it. It does this by using xposition2 and i as the position of the checked object, then using an if statement will determine if that position is occupied by a Room object. If it is, it returns false, if it is not, then it returns true.
        Parameters:
        xPosition2 - - int containing the x-coordinate of the position being checked
        i - - int containing the y-coordinate of the position being checked
        Returns:
        - boolean that is false when a Room exists, and true otherwise

      • upPossible

        public boolean upPossible()
        This method checks to ensure that there is no Room in the way of the Player when they attempt to move north. It does this by calling roomExists(int, int) passing pos[0] - 1 and pos[1] to it. Subtracting 1 from the position of the object's x-position will move it up one space. It returns a boolean that is true when roomExists(int, int) is false, and visa versa.
        Returns:
        - boolean that is true when roomExists(int, int) is false, and visa versa.

      • downPossible

        public boolean downPossible()
        This method checks to ensure that there is no Room in the way of the Player when they attempt to move south. It does this by calling roomExists(int, int) passing pos[0] + 1 and pos[1] to it. Adding 1 to the position of the object's x-position will move it down one space. It returns a boolean that is true when roomExists(int, int) is false, and visa versa.
        Returns:
        - boolean that is true when roomExists(int, int) is false, and visa versa.

      • rightPossible

        public boolean rightPossible()
        This method checks to ensure that there is no Room in the way of the Player when they attempt to move east. It does this by calling roomExists(int, int) passing pos[0] and pos[1]+ 1 to it. Adding 1 to the position of the object's y-position will move it right one space. It returns a boolean that is true when roomExists(int, int) is false, and visa versa.
        Returns:
        - boolean that is true when roomExists(int, int) is false, and visa versa.

      • leftPossible

        public boolean leftPossible()
        This method checks to ensure that there is no Room in the way of the Player when they attempt to move west. It does this by calling roomExists(int, int) passing pos[0] and pos[1]- 1 to it. Subtracting 1 from the position of the object's y-position will move it left one space. It returns a boolean that is true when roomExists(int, int) is false, and visa versa.
        Returns:
        - boolean that is true when roomExists(int, int) is false, and visa versa.
